    - class Boid with fields x, y, vx, vy, size, color; method update(boids, width, height, dt, speed) that applies classic boids rules (alignment, cohesion, separation) with internal constants, wraps at edges, and enforces constant speed magnitude 'speed' irrespective of size.
    - function spawnBoids(n, width, height, speed): returns array of Boid with random positions and directions; colorful hues; constant speed.
  Notes:
    - Internal constants only; no user-config UI.
    - Keep speed independent of size.
- js/simulation.js: Exports class Simulation:
    - constructor(width, height, count=300, speed=240) initializes boids via spawnBoids; stores bounds; methods:
        - update(dt) steps each boid with current bounds, dt, and constant speed.
        - resize(width, height) updates bounds and softly re-wraps boids into new bounds if they drift.
        - getBoids() or a 'boids' getter to expose the array.
- js/renderer.js: Exports class Renderer that:
    - constructor(ctx) stores 2D context; has a setSize(width, height) for CSS-px sizing.
    - clear() clears canvas; draw(boids) renders each boid as an oriented triangle pointing along velocity with its own color.
    - Assume context is already scaled to CSS pixels (handled in main.js).
- js/main.js: Entry point wired to index.html:
    - Grabs #boids-canvas, fits it to window with devicePixelRatio scaling (ctx.setTransform(dpr,0,0,dpr,0,0)); returns CSS-px width/height.
    - Instantiates Simulation(width,height,300,240) and Renderer(ctx).
    - Handles window resize to refit canvas and simulation/renderer sizes.
    - requestAnimationFrame loop computing dt in seconds (clamped), sim.update(dt), renderer.clear()+renderer.draw(sim.boids).
Inter-file contracts:
- main.js imports { Simulation } from "./simulation.js" and { Renderer } from "./renderer.js".
- simulation.js imports { Boid, spawnBoids } from "./boid.js".
- renderer.js relies on Boid objects having x,y,vx,vy,size,color and draws triangles.
- No external libs; plain ES modules.
"""

# Delegate index.html
h1 = delegate(
    "index_html",
    """You OWN exactly output/boids-simulation/index.html.
Write the full HTML per the contract:
- Minimal head with meta viewport, title "Boids Simulation", link to ./styles.css
- Body contains ONLY a <canvas id="boids-canvas"></canvas>
- Load <script type="module" src="./js/main.js"></script> at end of body.
Use a valid HTML5 structure.
write_file then done('ok').""",
    contract,
    model="fast",
)

# Delegate styles.css
h2 = delegate(
    "styles_css",
    """You OWN exactly output/boids-simulation/styles.css.
Write CSS to:
- Remove margins and scrollbars; full black background.
- Make canvas fill viewport (width:100vw; height:100vh) and display:block.
- Ensure smooth rendering; optionally set touch-action:none to avoid gestures.
write_file then done('ok').""",
    contract,
    model="fast",
)

# Delegate boid.js
h3 = delegate(
    "boid_js",
    """You OWN exactly output/boids-simulation/js/boid.js.
Implement per contract. Details:
- export class Boid { constructor(x, y, angle, speed, color) { ... } }
  Fields: x,y,vx,vy,size (e.g., 3.5), color (HSL string).
  Methods:
    - update(boids, width, height, dt, speed): applies alignment, cohesion, separation within radii
      Internal constants (no UI): PERCEPTION=55, SEPARATION_DIST=20, ALIGN_W=1.0, COHESION_W=0.8, SEPARATION_W=1.6, STEER=2.0 (blend rate 1/s).
      Compute neighbor aggregates; derive desired velocity directions for each rule; combine weights; blend current velocity toward the weighted desired using:
         vx += (desiredVx - vx) * STEER * dt
         vy += (desiredVy - vy) * STEER * dt
      Then renormalize (vx,vy) to magnitude 'speed' CONSTANT regardless of 'size'.
      Update position: x += vx * dt; y += vy * dt.
      Wrap around edges with a margin (2*size).
- export function spawnBoids(n, width, height, speed): returns array of Boid with random positions (0..width/height), random angle (0..2π), constant speed, vivid random hues (e.g., hsl(h,90%,60%)).
- Keep code efficient (no allocations in loops if possible); simple math is fine.
write_file then done('ok').""",
    contract,
    model="fast",
)

# Delegate simulation.js
h4 = delegate(
    "simulation_js",
    """You OWN exactly output/boids-simulation/js/simulation.js.
Implement per contract:
- import { Boid, spawnBoids } from "./boid.js";
- export class Simulation {
    constructor(width, height, count=300, speed=240) {
      this.width = width; this.height = height;
      this.speed = speed;
      this.boids = spawnBoids(count, width, height, speed);
    }
    update(dt) {
      const b = this.boids, w = this.width, h = this.height, s = this.speed;
      for (let i = 0; i < b.length; i++) b[i].update(b, w, h, dt, s);
    }
    resize(width, height) {
      this.width = width; this.height = height;
      // no re-spawn; boids will wrap into new bounds naturally
    }
    get boidsArray() { return this.boids; }
  }
- Ensure named export { Simulation }.
write_file then done('ok').""",
    contract,
    model="fast",
)

# Delegate renderer.js
h5 = delegate(
    "renderer_js",
    """You OWN exactly output/boids-simulation/js/renderer.js.
Implement per contract:
- export class Renderer {
    constructor(ctx) { this.ctx = ctx; this.width = 0; this.height = 0; }
    setSize(width, height){ this.width = width; this.height = height; }
    clear(){
      const ctx = this.ctx;
      ctx.clearRect(0, 0, this.width, this.height);
      // Optional subtle background:
      ctx.fillStyle = "#000";
      ctx.fillRect(0, 0, this.width, this.height);
    }
    draw(boids){
      const ctx = this.ctx;
      for (let i=0;i<boids.length;i++){
        const b = boids[i];
        const angle = Math.atan2(b.vy, b.vx);
        const s = b.size || 3.5;
        const head = s * 2.2;
        const wing = s * 1.2;
        const x = b.x, y = b.y;

        // Triangle points oriented along 'angle'
        const cos = Math.cos(angle), sin = Math.sin(angle);
        const x1 = x + cos * head,      y1 = y + sin * head;        // nose
        const x2 = x - cos * head + -sin * wing, y2 = y - sin * head +  cos * wing; // left
        const x3 = x - cos * head +  sin * wing, y3 = y - sin * head + -cos * wing; // right

        ctx.fillStyle = b.color || "#fff";
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(x1, y1);
        ctx.lineTo(x2, y2);
        ctx.lineTo(x3, y3);
        ctx.closePath();
        ctx.fill();
      }
    }
  }
- Ensure named export { Renderer }.
write_file then done('ok').""",
    contract,
    model="fast",
)

